<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><?ish ishref="GUID-079C6F04-73A7-4014-A371-1F45AFF92435" version="2" lang="en-US"?><task xmlns:ditaarch="http://dita.oasis-open.org/architecture/2005/" id="GUID-079C6F04-73A7-4014-A371-1F45AFF92435" xml:lang="en-US" ditaarch:DITAArchVersion="1.3" domains="(topic task)                            (topic hi-d)                            (topic ui-d)                            (topic sw-d)                            (topic indexing-d)                            (topic ut-d)                            a(base ishcondition)                            a(base varid)                            a(base varref)                            a(base cid)                            a(base partslist)                            (topic oce-d)                            (topic sdlVariables-c)                            (topic oceCommonElements-c)                            (topic oceMetaDecl-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c task oceTask-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c hi-d oceHighlight-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c ui-d oceUi-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c sw-d oceSoftware-c)   " class="- topic/topic task/task "><title class="- topic/title ">1958 Curing fault message reported</title><abstract class="- topic/abstract " id="GUID-7D7726BC-C48B-4613-A30A-E7D986B7E0FC"><p class="- topic/p ">This warning gives more information on the root cause of the lamp failure. The message can only be read in PRISMAservice (Technical views: standard -&gt; 20 events). 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">See the picture below. 
</p><fig class="- topic/fig " id="GUID-2AABD60A-7C4A-41AA-B20E-CC99ECE6576B"><title class="- topic/title "/><image class="- topic/image " href="GUID-9980E563-DF25-456C-8640-52198B0F4D9D-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" otherprops="GUID-9980E563-DF25-456C-8640-52198B0F4D9D-low.png"/></fig></abstract><prolog class="- topic/prolog "><metadata class="- topic/metadata "><category class="- topic/category ">Diagnostics</category></metadata></prolog><taskbody class="- topic/body task/taskbody "><section id="GUID-6F8D5E77-C086-49AC-826C-E0A491D2E7DF" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title "> The following messages can be shown:</title><ol class="- topic/ol "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> curingFaultMessage: &lt;number&gt;: Fault Evt=BlownFuse Sev=High Src=LAMPx.x (V= x.xx) 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">This indicates a defect fuse in the <comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">Lamp control PBA</compname><compcodenr translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr "> 01PBA03 </compcodenr></comp>. 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> Reason: the defect lamp will blow the fuse inside the lamp control pba. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Which lamp has to be replaced is indicated by warning 1956/1957 (see PRISMAservice). 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Warning 1956 -&gt; replace <comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">Pre curing lamp PBA</compname><compcodenr translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr "> 01PBA01 </compcodenr><compsignal translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compsignal ">PRE_CURE_LAMP</compsignal></comp>
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Warning 1957 -&gt; replace <comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">Pin Post Cure lamp PBA (UV LED lamp 75/50)</compname><compcodenr translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr "> 01PBA02 </compcodenr><compsignal translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compsignal ">POST_PIN_CURE_LAMP</compsignal></comp>.
</p><p class="- topic/p "><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Action</b>: replace <comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">Lamp control PBA</compname><compcodenr translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr "> 01PBA03 </compcodenr></comp> and the indicated lamp. 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> curingFaultMessage: &lt;number&gt;: Fault Evt=FalseCurrent Sev=High Src=LAMPx.x (I=xx.xx) 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">The controller measures a led current while the lamp enable is off. 
</p><p class="- topic/p "><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Action</b>: replace <comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">Lamp control PBA</compname><compcodenr translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr "> 01PBA03 </compcodenr></comp>. 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> curingFaultMessage: &lt;number&gt;: Fault Evt=UnderVoltage Sev=High Src=LAMPx.x (V=x.xx) 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">This indicates a voltage lower than 44 Volt inside the <comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">Lamp control PBA</compname><compcodenr translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr "> 01PBA03 </compcodenr></comp>. 
</p><p class="- topic/p "><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Action</b>: 
</p><ol class="- topic/ol "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> Enable <comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">48 VDC Supply Curing</compname><compcodenr translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr "> 22G04 </compcodenr><compsignal translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compsignal ">48V_CUR/1</compsignal></comp> in cold sds with 
<xref keyref="SDS22-6-104" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-E6C1D680-E3F7-4C27-A6A6-6719294A7178.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="task"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text xref?>22-6-104 Check PSU 22G04 (48V Curing) [Special Tests]</xref>. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Measure if the <comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">48 VDC Supply Curing</compname><compcodenr translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr "> 22G04 </compcodenr><compsignal translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compsignal ">48V_CUR/1</compsignal></comp> is within spec (47 V &lt; Vsupply &lt; 49 V) 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> If power supply is ok, replace <comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">Lamp control PBA</compname><compcodenr translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr "> 01PBA03 </compcodenr></comp>. 
</p></li></ol></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> curingFaultMessage: &lt;number&gt;: Fault Evt=OverVoltage Sev=High Src=LAMPx.x (V=x.xx) 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">This indicates a voltage higher than 52 Volt inside the <comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">Lamp control PBA</compname><compcodenr translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr "> 01PBA03 </compcodenr></comp>. 
</p><p class="- topic/p "><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Action</b>: 
</p><ol class="- topic/ol "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> Enable <comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">48 VDC Supply Curing</compname><compcodenr translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr "> 22G04 </compcodenr><compsignal translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compsignal ">48V_CUR/1</compsignal></comp> in cold sds with 
<xref keyref="SDS22-6-104" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-E6C1D680-E3F7-4C27-A6A6-6719294A7178.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="task"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text xref?>22-6-104 Check PSU 22G04 (48V Curing) [Special Tests]</xref>. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Measure if the <comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">48 VDC Supply Curing</compname><compcodenr translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr "> 22G04 </compcodenr><compsignal translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compsignal ">48V_CUR/1</compsignal></comp> is within spec (47 V &lt; Vsupply &lt; 49 V) 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> If power supply is ok, replace <comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">Lamp control PBA</compname><compcodenr translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr "> 01PBA03 </compcodenr></comp>. 
</p></li></ol></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> curingFaultMessage: &lt;number&gt;: Fault Evt=OverTemperature Sev=High Src=LAMPx.x (T=xx.xx) 
</p><p class="- topic/p "><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Action</b>: 
</p><ol class="- topic/ol "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> Check the cooling system (hose connections, cooling tubes, chiller). See error 1503/1506. (<xref keyref="E1503" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-630B1128-D3E8-4B9D-B08C-6AC76F7198CC.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="tsTroubleshooting"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text xref?>1503 Temperature pre-curing lamp (01PBA01) too high</xref>/<xref keyref="E1506" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-3E053682-3D1E-4DEA-81B1-9408024DF749.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="tsTroubleshooting"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text xref?>1506 Temperature post and pin curing lamp (01PBA02) too high</xref>) 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> If cooling system is ok, replace the lamp (temperature measurement inside lamp is defect). The faulty lamp is indicated by error 1956/1957. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">In some cases the temperature reading indicates extreme temperatures, in that case the lamp is defect and must be replaced. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Warning 1956 -&gt; replace <comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">Pre curing lamp PBA</compname><compcodenr translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr "> 01PBA01 </compcodenr><compsignal translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compsignal ">PRE_CURE_LAMP</compsignal></comp>. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Warning 1957 -&gt; replace <comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">Pin Post Cure lamp PBA (UV LED lamp 75/50)</compname><compcodenr translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr "> 01PBA02 </compcodenr><compsignal translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compsignal ">POST_PIN_CURE_LAMP</compsignal></comp>. 
</p></li></ol></li></ol></section></taskbody><related-links class="- topic/related-links "><linkpool class="- topic/linkpool " mapkeyref="GUID-8A41CFEA-5928-4042-A2CB-507A5D034160"><link class="- topic/link " mapclass="- map/topicref " format="dita" type="concept" href="generated-topic-GUID-F00C2AB0-7ECC-4440-8B16-0DBCB1EB3BF2.xml" role="parent"><?ditaot usertext?><linktext class="- topic/linktext "><?ditaot usertext?>Diagnostics</linktext></link></linkpool></related-links>
</task>